title: Population of Europe 2016 , by country and gender
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 40 different Countrys on X-axis for 2 groups Male, and Female. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Number of inhabitants.
For Country Germany, Female had the highest Number of inhabitants 41661561.0 among the 2 groups and in Liechtenstein, Male had the lowest Number of inhabitants 18660.0.
The maximum Number of inhabitants for Female that was found in Country Germany was 2197.11 times larger than the minimum Number of inhabitants observed in Country Liechtenstein.
Averaging all 2 groups Male, and Female, the Country Germany is the maximum Number of inhabitants and Liechtenstein is the minimum Number of inhabitants.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart shows Number of inhabitants on the Y-axis for 40 different Countrys for 2 groups Male, and Female that are presented on the X-axis.
Out of all 2 groups, Female had the highest Number of inhabitants for Country Germany and Male had the lowest Number of inhabitants for Country Liechtenstein.
Among all the Countrys, Female had the highest Number of inhabitants in Country Germany and lowest Number of inhabitants in Country Liechtenstein.
Country Germany and Liechtenstein had the biggest gap of 41642599.0 between the highest and lowest Number of inhabitants found for Female.
Among all 2 groups, Male had the gap of 40495463.0 between the maximum and minimum Number of inhabitants observed in Country Germany and Liechtenstein respectively.
On average, the Country Germany had the highest Number of inhabitants for all 2 groups Male, and Female. Whereas Liechtenstein had the lowest average Number of inhabitants.
